 |accessdate=2020-04-03}}</ref>\n* '' [[Arnold Palmer]]''.  Statue (Bronze | over-life size). [[Arnold Palmer Airport]], [[Latrobe, Pennsylvania]]; Laurel Valley Country Club, Ligonier, Pennsylvania; Tralee, Ireland.\n* '' [[Jack Nicklaus]]''.  Statue (Bronze, granite base | 48 inches). [[USGA Museum]], Jack Nicklaus Room, [[Far Hills, New Jersey]]. Dedication: May 27, 2015. <ref>{{Cite web| author= United States Golf Association | url =https://www.usga.org/content/usga/home-page/videos/2015/05/27/150527-nicklaus-room-wrap-4260846447001.html| title=Jack Nicklaus Room Opening|accessdate=2020-04-01}}</ref>\n* '' [[Jack Nicklaus]]''.  Portrait bust (Bronze, stone base | life size). Private collection.\n* '' [[Jack Nicklaus]] and Dwight Gahm''.  Statue (Bronze | life size). [[Valhalla Golf Club]], [[Louisville, Kentucky]]. Dedication: March 8, 2016. <ref>{{Cite web| author= '' Golf Digest'' | url =https://www.golfdigest.com/story/valhalla-golf-club-founder-dies-jack-nicklaus-pays-tribute | title=Valhalla Golf Club Founder Dies, Jack Nicklaus Pays Tribute|accessdate=2020-04-04}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web| author= Zak, Sean, ''Golf''  | url =https://www.golf.com/tour-and-news/jack-nicklaus-marks-passing-friend-valhalla-owner-dwight-gahm | title=Jack Nicklaus Marks Passing of Friend, Valhalla Founder Dwight Gahm |accessdate=2020-04-04}}</ref>\n* '' [[Dinah Shore]] Wall of Champions''.  Relief sculpture (Bronze, Cantera stone | life size). Mission Hills Country Club and Resort, [[Rancho Mirage, California]]. Dedication: March 26, 1995. <ref>{{Cite web| author= Baldwin, Patricia, ''South Florida Sun-Sentinel'' | url =https://www.sun-sentinel.com/news/fl-xpm-1995-03-26-9503250301-story.html | title=Wall of Champions is a Fitting Memorial to Dinah| accessdate=2020-04-04}}</ref>\n* '' [[Robert H. Dedman Sr.]]''.  Statue (Bronze | 7ft | sculpted from life). [[Pinehurst Resort]], [[North Carolina]]. <ref>{{Cite web| author= Waymarking'' | url =https://www.waymarking.com/waymarks/WMD79G_Robert_H_Dedman_Sr_Pinehurst_NC | title= Robert H. Dedman Sr. \u2013 Pinehurst, NC \u2013 Statues of Historic Figures| accessdate=2020-04-04}}</ref>\n* '' [[Richard Tufts]]''.  Statue (Bronze | over-life size). Walk of Fame, [[Pinehurst Resort]], [[North Carolina]]. <ref>{{Cite web| author= Waymarking'' | url =https://www.waymarking.com/waymarks/WMD738_Richard_Tufts_Pinehurst_Golf_Course_Pinehurst_NC | title= Richard Tufts \u2013 Pinehurst, NC \u2013 Statues of Historic Figures| accessdate=2020-04-04}}</ref>\n* '' [[Bobby Jones (golfer)|Bob Jones]]''.  Portrait bust (Bronze | life size). [[East Lake Golf Club]], [[Atlanta, Georgia]].\n* '' [[Bobby Jones (golfer)|Bob Jones]]''.  Statue (Bronze | over-life-size). Georgia Golf Hall of Fame, [[Augusta, Georgia]]. <ref>{{Cite web| author= The Masters | url =http://usatoday30.usatoday.com/sports/golf/masters01/2001-03-30-statues.html| title=Statues of Legends Find Home in New Augusta| accessdate=2020-03-30}}</ref>\n* '' [[Bobby Jones (golfer)|Bob Jones]]''.  Distinguished Sportsman Award (Bronze | 18in). Bob Jones, [[U.S. Golf Association]] Museum.\n====Baseball====\n* '' [[Mike Schmidt]]''.  Portrait bust (Bronze | life size | sculpted from life). Private collection.<ref name=\"baseball\">{{Cite web| author= Tierney, Mike, \u201cThe New York Times'' | url =https://www.nytimes.com/2011/09/21/sports/baseball/baseballs-bronze-age.html?_r=0 | title= In Baseball\u2019s Bronze Age, Statues Are Becoming Bigger Part of Landscape | accessdate=2020-04-10}}</ref>\n* '' [[Mike Schmidt]]''.  Statue (Bronze | 10 ft | sculpted from life). [[Citizens Bank Park]], [[Philadelphia, Pennsylvania]]. Dedication: 12/4/2004.<ref name=\"baseball\" /><ref>{{Cite web| author= \u201cThe Sporting Statues Project'' | url = http://www.offbeat.group.shef.ac.uk/statues/STUS_Schmidt_Mike.htm | title= Mike Schmidt | accessdate=2020-04-10}}</ref>\n* '' [[Steve Carlton]]''.  Statue (Bronze | 10 ft | sculpted from life). [[Citizens Bank Park]], [[Philadelphia, Pennsylvania]]. Dedication: 12/4/2004.<ref name=\"baseball\" /><ref>{{Cite web| author= \u201cThe Sporting Statues Project'' | url = http://www.offbeat.group.shef.ac.uk/statues/STUS_Ashburn_Richie.htm | title= Steve Carlton | accessdate=2020-04-10}}</ref>\n* '' [[Richie Ashburn]]''.  Statue (Bronze | 10 ft | sculpted from life). [[Citizens Bank Park]], [[Philadelphia, Pennsylvania]]. Dedication: 12/4/2004.<ref name=\"baseball\" /><ref>{{Cite web| author= \u201cThe Sporting Statues Project'' | url = http://www.offbeat.group.shef.ac.uk/statues/STUS_Ashburn_Richie.htm | title= Richie Ashburn | accessdate=2020-04-10}}</ref>\n* '' [[Robin Roberts (baseball)|Robin Roberts]]''.  Statue (Bronze | 10 ft | sculpted from life). [[Citizens Bank Park]], [[Philadelphia, Pennsylvania]]. Dedication: 12/4/2004.<ref name=\"baseball\" /><ref>{{Cite web| author= \u201cThe Sporting Statues Project'' | url = http://www.offbeat.group.shef.ac.uk/statues/STUS_Roberts_Robin.htm | title= Robin Roberts | accessdate=2020-04-10}}</ref>\n* '' [[Joe DiMaggio]] and Young Boy''.  Statue (Bronze | over-life-size | sculpted from life). DiMaggio Children's Hospital, [[Hollywood, Florida]]. Dedication: 10/10/2002.<ref>{{Cite web| author= \u201cThe Sporting Statues Project'' | url = http://www.offbeat.group.shef.ac.uk/statues/STUS_DiMaggio_Joe_2.htm | title= Joe DeMaggio | accessdate=2020-04-10}}</ref>\n* '' [[Danny Murtaugh]] '' Relief sculpture, Boston Braves, 1947 (Bronze | relief | 28 x 34 | over 100 lbs.). [[Pennsylvania Sports Hall of Fame | Athletes Hall of Fame]], [[Chadds Ford, Pennsylvania]]. Dedication: Nov. 20, 2011.<ref>{{Cite web| author= Lougue, Timothy, \u201cDaily Times'' | url = https://www.delcotimes.com/news/vernon-history-museum-honors-danny-murtaugh/article_161dc1b9-4617-5a33-a684-a79f9ec41271.html | title= Vernon History Museum Honors Danny Murtaugh | accessdate=2020-04-10}}</ref>\n\n====Hockey====\n* '' [[Brian Propp]]''.  Portrait bust (Bronze | life size). [[Philadelphia Flyers]] Hall of Fame. Additional casting in private collection.\n\n====Coaches====\n* '' Coach Fritz Brennan'' Statue (Bronze | 8ft). Lower Merion High School Arnold Field, Montgomery Avenue, [[Ardmore, Pennsylvania]]. Completed: 1990 .<ref>{{Cite web| author= \u201cSmithsonian'' | url =https://www.si.edu/object/siris_ari_327906 | title= John \"Fritz\" Brennan, (sculpture) | accessdate=2020-04-10}}</ref>\n* '' [[Ron Fraser | Coach Ron Fraser]] '' Statue (Bronze | 7ft). [[University of Miami]], [[Miami, Florida]]. Dedication: April 24, 2015.<ref>{{Cite web| author= Kaufman, Michelle, \u201cMiami Herald'' | url =https://www.miamiherald.com/sports/college/acc/university-of-miami/article19433436.html | title= \u2018More than just a coach\u2019: UM legend Ron Fraser honored with statue during emotional ceremony | accessdate=2020-04-10}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web| author= \u201cThe Sporting Statues Project'' | url = http://www.offbeat.group.shef.ac.uk/statues/STUS_Fraser_Ron.htm | title= Ron Fraser | accessdate=2020-04-10}}</ref>\n* '' Coach \u201cLake\u201d Staffieri '' Relief (Bronze | life size). Franklin Field, [[University of Pennsylvania]], [[Philadelphia, Pennsylvania]]. Dedication: 2010. <ref>{{Cite web| author= Labbe, Dan , \u201cCleveland.com'' | url =https://www.cleveland.com/browns/2020/01/browns-head-coach-kevin-stefanski-always-stood-out-during-his-days-in-philadelphia-even-when-he-wasnt-trying-to-stand-out.html | title= Browns head coach Kevin Stefanski always stood out during his days in Philadelphia, even when he wasn\u2019t trying to stand out | accessdate=2020-04-10}}</ref>\n\n\n===Statues===\n* '' [[Clarence Darrow]]''. Statue (Bronze | 7ft) [[Rhea County Courthouse]], [[Dayton, Tennessee]]. Dedication: July 14, 2017. <ref>{{Cite web| author= Fausset, Richard, The New York Times | url =https://www.nytimes.com/2017/07/14/us/darrow-bryan-dayton-tennessee-scopes-statues.html| title=At Site of Scopes Trial, Darrow Statue Belatedly Joins Bryan\u2019s |accessdate=2020-04-01}}</ref>\n*''[[Frederick Law Olmsted]]''. Statue (Bronze, stone base | 8ft) Blue Ridge Court, [[The North Carolina Arboretum]], [[Asheville, North Carolina]]. Dedication: April 22, 2015.<ref>{{Cite web| author= Citizen Times | url =https://www.citizen-times.com/story/news/local/2015/02/02/arboretum-prepares-olmsted-statue-expected-fall/22738735/ | title=Arboretum prepares for Olmsted statue |accessdate=2020-04-01}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web| author= National Sculpture Society | url =https://nationalsculpture.org/news-events/frederick-law-olmsted/ | title=Frederick Law Olmsted |accessdate=2020-04-11}}</ref>\n* '' [[Michael Kahn (theatre director)|Michael Kahn]]''.  former Artistic Director, Shakespeare Theatre Company. Statue (Bronze | life size) Sidney Harman Hall, [[Shakespeare Theatre Company]], [[Washington, DC.]] Private Collection. Completed: 2012.<ref>{{Cite web| author= Rosenstein, Peter, The Georgetown Dish | url =http://www.thegeorgetowndish.com/thedish/michael-kahn-leader-innovator-icon-friend | title=Michael Kahn; Leader, Innovator, Icon, Friend | accessdate=2020-04-01}}</ref> \n* '' [[John D. MacArthur]]''.  Statue (Bronze, granite base | 8ft figure, 3ft base | 750lbs) [[Palm Beach Gardens]], [[North Palm Beach, Florida]]. Dedication: November 21, 2010.<ref>{{Cite web| author= DiPaolo, Bill, The Palm Beach Post | url =https://www.palmbeachpost.com/news/macarthur-statue-arrives-final-resting-place-palm-beach-gardens/KiAt4rqroyoAQbuUADKR1I/ | title=MacArthur statue arrives at final resting place in Palm Beach Gardens |accessdate=2020-04-01}}</ref>\n\n\n===Portrait Busts===\n====Contemporary====\n* '' [[Don McLean]]''. American singer-songwriter. Portrait bust (Bronze | life size). Used on 1992 album ''Don McLean Classics''. Private collection.<ref>{{Cite web| author= Freeman, Jarreau, ''Daily Local News\"  | url =https://www.dailylocal.com/lifestyle/zenos-frudakis-known-for-freedom-says-art-is-his-way/article_d58d5c7d-c381-534e-bef5-e1e306a593cd.html | title=Zenos Frudakis, known for \u2018Freedom,\u2019 says art is his way of cheating death|accessdate=2020-04-06}}</ref>\n* '' [[Jacques P\u00e9pin]]''. French-American Chef, author, culinary educator, telivision personality, artist. Portrait bust (Bronze | life size). Stone Acres Farm. Dedication: October 13, 2019.<ref>{{Cite web| author= ''National Sculpture Society\" | url =https://nationalsculpture.org/news-events/jacques-pepin/ | title=Jacques Pepin |accessdate=2020-04-10}}</ref>\n* '' [[Philip Cohen]]''. Portrait bust (Clay, cast in plaster | life size). Private collection.\n* '' [[Paul Girolami|Sir Paul Girolami]]''. British-Italian businessman, CEO of Glaxo, Inc. Portrait bust (Bronze | life size). Research Triangle Park, [[North Carolina]]; [[London, England]]; [[Tokyo, Japan]].\n* '' [[John D. MacArthur]]''. American Businessman and philanthropist. Portrait bust (Bronze, granite base | life size). Private collection.\n* '' [[Edmund N. Bacon]]''. American urban planner, architect, educator and author. Portrait bust (Bronze | life size). Private collection.\n* '' Samuel L. Evans''. Civil rights activist, education innovator, community service advocate, chamber music impresario. Founder of the American Foundation for Negro Affairs (AFNA). Portrait bust (Bronze, wood base | life size). AFNA, [[Philadelphia, Pennsylvania]]. Dedication: May 27, 2015. <ref>{{Cite web| author= Temple Universities Libraries | url =https://library.temple.edu/finding_aids/samuel-l-evans-papers| title=Samuel L. Evans Papers|accessdate=2020-04-05}}</ref>\n* '' [[Nina Simone]]''. American singer, songwriter, musician, arranger and civil rights activist. Portrait bust (Bronze | over-life size). Private collection.<ref name=\"Simone\"></ref>\n* '' Sheila''.  Portrait bust (Bronze | life size). Museum of the Academy of Design, Permanent Collection. [[National Academy of Design]], [[New York, New York]].\n* '' Dr. Stone''.  Portrait bust (Bronze | life size). [[Temple University School of Medicine]], [[Philadelphia, Pennsylvania]].\n* '' [[Norman Adrian Wiggins | Dr. Norman Adrian Wiggins]]''. President of Campbell University, 1967-2003. Portrait bust (Bronze | life size). Dr. Norman Adrian Wiggins School of Law, [[Campbell University]], [[Raleigh, North Carolina]].\n* '' [[Robert H. Dedman, Sr.]]''. Businessman, philanthropist. Portrait bust (Bronze | life size | sculpted from life). Southern Methodist University,  Dedman School of Law. Additional castings, private collections.\n* '' Rosalie Frudakis''.  Portrait bust (Bronze | life size). Private collection.\n* '' Mr. Mederios''.  Portrait bust (Bronze | life size | sculpted from life). Private collection.\n* '' Mrs. Mederios''. Portrait bust (Bronze | life size | sculpted from life). Private collection.\n* '' Mr. Cognetta''. Portrait bust (Bronze | life size | sculpted from life). Private collection, Cemetery, [[Stamford, Connecticut]].\n\n====Government/Military====\n* '' [[Ulysses S. Grant | General Grant]]''. 18th President of the United States, U.S. Secretary of War, 6th Commanding General of the U.S. Army. Portrait bust (Bronze | over-life-size) The Lotos Club, [[New York City|New York]], New York.\n* '' [[Dwight D. Eisenhower]]''. 34th President of the United States, General of the U.S. Army. Portrait bust (Bronze | life size). Private collection.\n* '' [[Winston Churchill]]''. Prime Minister of the United Kingdom. Portrait bust (Bronze | life size). Private collection.\n* '' [[Alexander Hamilton]]''. First U.S. Secretary of the Treasury, Founding Father of U.S., Military Commander. Portrait bust (Bronze | life size). Private collection.\n* '' [[Benjamin Franklin]]''. Founding Father of U.S., U.S. Minister to France and Sweden. Portrait bust (Clay | life size). Private collection.\n* '' [[A. A. Birch Jr. | Chief Justice Birch]]''. American lawyer and judge,,first African American to serve as Chief Justice of the Tennessee Supreme Court. Portrait bust (Bronze | life size). [[Tennessee Supreme Court]], [[Nashville, Tennessee]].\n* '' [[John Sevier]]''. First Governor of Tennessee, Portrait bust (Bronze | life size). Sevier Public Library, King Family Library, [[Sevierville, Tennessee]]. Additional castings in private collections.<ref>{{Cite web| author= Mountain Press | url =http://mountainpress.uber.matchbin.net/printer_friendly/7369160| title=Jack Sevier Statue to Make Library Truly Complete|accessdate=2020-04-05}}</ref>\n* '' [[William P. Yarborough | General Yarborough]]''. Senior U.S. Army officer, \"Father of the Modern Green Berets.\" Designed U.S. Army's parachutist badge, paratrooper boots and airborne jump uniform. Portrait bust (Bronze | life size). [[Airborne & Special Operations Museum]], [[Fayetteville, North Carolina]].\n* '' [[K. Leroy Irvis]]''. Teacher, activist, politician. First African American to serve as speaker of the house in U.S. state legislature since Reconstruction. Portrait bust (Bronze | life size). State Museum of Pennsylvania, [[Harrisburg, Pennsylvania]]. Additional castings in private collections.\n* '' [[United States Marine Corps|Marine]]''. U.S. Marine killed in Iraq. Portrait bust (Bronze | life size). Private collection.\n\n====Historic====\n* ''[[Mark Twain]]''. American writer, humorist, entrepreneur, publisher and lecturer. Portrait bust. (Bronze | over-life-size) The Lotos Club, [[New York City|New York]], New York.<ref>\"The Lotos Experience 1995 pp. 34-35\"</ref>\n* '' [[Albert Einstein]]''. Theoretical physicist. Portrait bust (Clay | life size). Studio collection.\n* '' [[Amelia Earhart]]''. American aviation pioneer and author. Portrait bust (Clay | life size). Studio collection.\n* '' [[Ralph Waldo Emerson]]''. American essayist, lecturer, philosopher and poet. Portrait bust (Clay | life size). Studio collection.\n* '' [[Edgar Allan Poe]],'' American writer, poet, editor and literary critic. Portrait bust (Clay | life size). Studio collection.\n* '' [[Dante Alighieri | Dante]]''. Italian poet. Portrait bust (Clay | life size). Studio collection.\n\n\n==Awards==\nFrudakis is a member of the prestigious [[National Sculpture Society]].<ref name=nss_fellow>{{Cite web| author=National Sculpture Society| url=https://nationalsculpture.org/author/zenos_frudakis/| title= Fellows of NSS |accessdate=2012-03-30}}</ref>\n\nIn 1990, Frudakis was invited to participate in Japan's Third Rodin Grand Prize Exhibition, where he won the Hakone Award at Utsukushi-ga-hara Open Air Museum.<ref>Third Rodin Grand Prize Exhibit, The Utsukushi-ga-hara Open Air Museum, Hakone Open Air Museum, Embassies of Greece, Spain, United Kingdom and British Consul, United States, West Germany, 1990, pp. 27-28.</ref> The Museum purchased a cast of Frudakis's sculpture ''Reaching''.<ref>Donald Reynolds, ''Masters of American Sculpture'' (Abbeville Press, 1993), p. 250.</ref>\n\nIn 1991 he was elected into the [[National Academy of Design]] as an Associate member, and became a full Academician in 1993.\n\n\n==Gallery==\n<gallery mode=\"packed\" heights=\"200\">\n<!-- Deleted image removed: Image:Zenos_Frudakis_Dream_To_Fly_Cherry_Hill.jpg|Dream to Fly, Cherry Hill, NJ -->\nImage:Knowledge is Power.jpg|thumb|Knowledge is Power.\nImage:Zenos_Frudakis_Gateway_to_Growth_in_progress.JPG|Gateway to Growth (in progress)\nImage:Chef Pep\u00edn, portrait sculpture and sculptor Zenos Frudakis.jpg|Chef Pepin, portrait sculpture and Frudakis\nImage:Zenos_Frudakis_General_Yarborough_Fayetteville.JPG|General Yarborough, Airborne & Special Ops Museum, Fayetteville, NC\nImage:Zenos_Frudakis_Jack_Nicklaus_Louisville.jpg|[[Jack Nicklaus]], Dwight Gahm [[Valhalla Golf Club]], Louisville, KY\nImage:Dwight Eisenhower sculpture by Zenos Frudakis.jpg|thumb|Portrait sculpture of Dwight D. Eisenhower by Zenos Frudakis.\nImage:Zenos_Frudakis_Mark_Twain_Lotos.jpg|[[Mark Twain]], The [[Lotos Club]], New York, NY\nImage:Pennsylvania Anthracite Miners Memorial, Shenandoah PA 01.JPG|Pennsylvania Anthracite Miners Memorial in Shenandoah,